1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:07,048
Here.

2
00:00:08,133 --> 00:00:10,635
-Is it ready? Is it running?
-Yeah. Filming.

3
00:00:10,719 --> 00:00:12,637
-How do you know?
-I made it film.

4
00:00:12,721 --> 00:00:15,348
-I'm walking!
-Okay, let go. Let go.

5
00:00:15,432 --> 00:00:17,767
Come here, Nick. Come here.

6
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:21,187
Let him go.

7
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:25,066
-He's walking!
-There he is!

8
00:00:25,150 --> 00:00:29,029
All right! Cookin' it up,
but check it out who's cooking.

9
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:34,367
People say, "Hulk Hogan,
we know you've got a lot of things going."

10
00:00:34,451 --> 00:00:36,953
Say happy birthday to Nicky.

11
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:39,372
"You got family.
You got other ventures out there."

12
00:00:40,248 --> 00:00:41,624
"Are you gonna retire?"

13
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:46,755
When I sit here and actually think
about my last match at WrestleMania,

14
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:48,798
it chills me to the bone.

15
00:00:53,428 --> 00:00:57,140
Yes. Sure. Absolutely.

16
00:00:57,223 --> 00:01:00,769
-"Hogan's gonna retire."
-I won't know till I come out of the ring.

17
00:01:00,852 --> 00:01:01,978
Bullshit.

18
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:03,313
Fuck no.

19
00:01:03,396 --> 00:01:05,648
He had a ten-year retirement tour.

20
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:11,112
I curse the dark
And I pray for the light…

21
00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:14,532
Hulk Hogan is going
to stop wrestling at WrestleMania.

22
00:01:14,616 --> 00:01:16,117
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

23
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:17,660
No, he isn't.

24
00:01:17,744 --> 00:01:20,538
-Thank you for Hulkamania.
-Thank you.

25
00:01:20,622 --> 00:01:23,458
He'd always say,
"This is probably the last one."

26
00:01:23,541 --> 00:01:26,169
And then it was like,
"No, no, no, fuck that."

27
00:01:26,252 --> 00:01:27,962
He'd go crazy if he had to do that.

28
00:01:28,046 --> 00:01:31,883
A year ago, you and I speculated
on the future of Hulkamania.

29
00:01:31,966 --> 00:01:33,384
I want to change that around now.

30
00:01:33,468 --> 00:01:35,637
You know something?
I've been thinking about coming back.

31
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:38,139
-Ooh!
-For all the right reasons.

32
00:01:38,223 --> 00:01:41,392
My daughter was there when I won
the WWE Championship in WrestleMania.

33
00:01:41,476 --> 00:01:43,895
She saw Ric Flair say
he was the real world champion.

34
00:01:43,978 --> 00:01:45,146
Why were you crying?

35
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:48,149
She burst into tears.
She says, "Daddy, he's got your belt."

36
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:50,735
…so easy to ignore

37
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:52,821
Is that what I was fighting for?

38
00:01:52,904 --> 00:01:55,198
He's fighting for his life.

39
00:01:55,281 --> 00:01:57,242
No one has gotten up from that!

40
00:01:57,325 --> 00:01:59,869
Walking on a thin line…

41
00:02:01,162 --> 00:02:05,500
Being Hulk Hogan,
that's like being master of the universe.

42
00:02:06,417 --> 00:02:08,503
When you're a top guy like that,

43
00:02:08,586 --> 00:02:10,922
you wanna keep that spot.
It's like a drug.

44
00:02:11,005 --> 00:02:13,174
Walking on a thin line…

45
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:17,929
Even the other day, he was saying,
"I was thinking about one more match."

46
00:02:18,012 --> 00:02:21,266
You know? And I'm like,
"All right, here we go."

47
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:37,824
-Morning.
-Hey.

48
00:02:37,907 --> 00:02:38,950
-How you doing?
-All right.

49
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:40,076
All right.

50
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,077
Howdy.

51
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:42,996
-How you doing?
-Good, how are you?

52
00:02:43,079 --> 00:02:45,248
-Good.
-Mr. Hulk Hogan!

53
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:46,457
It was the '90s.

54
00:02:46,541 --> 00:02:52,005
And so his career at that point in time
was just like hurricane-strength famous.

55
00:02:52,088 --> 00:02:54,924
And there was just no room for error.

56
00:03:01,306 --> 00:03:03,474
Sounds like Madison Square Garden here.

57
00:03:03,558 --> 00:03:04,767
Boy, I'm tellin' you.

58
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:06,936
For the last five years,

59
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:10,064
the kids have been training
and saying their prayers.

60
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:13,818
And, uh, now that we've got
Hulkamania vitamins,

61
00:03:13,902 --> 00:03:15,778
I think the sky's the limit
with this thing.

62
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:22,785
Anybody that knew Terry
knew he was a health buff.

63
00:03:22,869 --> 00:03:26,664
He woke up and must have taken, like,
I don't know, 100 vitamins every day.

64
00:03:26,748 --> 00:03:30,460
We had to carve out a whole cupboard
in my kitchen for his vitamins.

65
00:03:30,543 --> 00:03:32,921
I wanna give you guys
a little dose of the medicine here.

66
00:03:33,004 --> 00:03:35,673
Once you get hooked on this stuff,
there's no return.

67
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:40,136
I would not advise this, obviously,
for anyone to…

68
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:41,596
That's incredible.

69
00:03:41,679 --> 00:03:43,890
He trained, said his prayers.

70
00:03:43,973 --> 00:03:47,560
We said a prayer every night.
He took his vitamins. It was so simple.

71
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:49,395
So he made that kind of his mantra.

72
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:51,105
If you train, pray, eat your vitamins,

73
00:03:51,189 --> 00:03:53,775
the first thing you know,
you'll be ripping out in the backjack.

74
00:03:53,858 --> 00:03:56,527
If you train, if you say your prayers,
if you eat your vitamins, man,

75
00:03:56,611 --> 00:03:58,238
sooner or later, you'll get what you want.

76
00:03:58,321 --> 00:04:01,157
Those are the three demandments
to be a Hulkamaniac.

77
00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:03,368
-Demandments?
-Demandments. Yes, sir.

78
00:04:03,451 --> 00:04:04,994
-Be a Hulkster.
-Wonderful.

79
00:04:06,788 --> 00:04:10,375
He was already doing that,
and he thought, "Why not?"

80
00:04:10,458 --> 00:04:14,003
If you know what Hulkamania is all about,
the training, the prayer, the vitamins,

81
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:17,465
you should've known that the Hulkster
would never sell out, brother.

82
00:04:18,716 --> 00:04:22,679
You know how he used to tell
kids to take their vitamins and all that?

83
00:04:23,429 --> 00:04:25,890
What are we talking about?
Orals or injectables?

84
00:04:25,974 --> 00:04:28,893
What kind of vitamins we talking here?

85
00:04:28,977 --> 00:04:31,938
Most of us think of professional wrestling
as harmless entertainment

86
00:04:32,021 --> 00:04:33,898
and Hulk Hogan as the king of the ring.

87
00:04:33,982 --> 00:04:37,277
But was there
a sinister side to his success?

88
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:40,613
He's taken steroids
through the whole decade of the '80s.

89
00:04:40,697 --> 00:04:46,035
The '80s were when steroids
really injected itself into wrestling.

90
00:04:46,119 --> 00:04:50,248
Back then, the mindset was
steroids were safer than sugar.

91
00:04:51,582 --> 00:04:52,917
They were legal.

92
00:04:53,001 --> 00:04:55,962
I first started using
two or three years after high school.

93
00:04:57,255 --> 00:05:01,259
I just kept getting bigger
and bigger and bigger and bigger.

94
00:05:01,342 --> 00:05:02,844
I'd be getting ready for school,

95
00:05:02,927 --> 00:05:04,804
and Dad would be down in the gym at 7:15.

96
00:05:04,887 --> 00:05:07,598
7:30 in the morning.
We're already in the gym.

97
00:05:07,682 --> 00:05:11,102
We're trying to get Brutus's body
as hard as his head.

98
00:05:11,185 --> 00:05:13,229
I'm going to do the thing…

99
00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:14,564
Right now.

100
00:05:14,647 --> 00:05:17,191
I had Ultimate Warrior
going out one door puking.

101
00:05:17,275 --> 00:05:19,193
-Yeah.
-Brutus started puking blood.

102
00:05:19,277 --> 00:05:22,947
You know, you need to do a few more.
I respect this guy right here.

103
00:05:23,031 --> 00:05:29,662
The thing is, when I was taking steroids,
I was between 300 and 348 pounds.

104
00:05:29,746 --> 00:05:30,580
Yeah.

105
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:34,083
But in the early 90s, there was
a bunch of controversy about steroids,

106
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:35,418
and the laws had changed.

107
00:05:35,501 --> 00:05:38,796
Tougher federal penalties against steroids
took effect in February.

108
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:41,132
A drug bust in Phoenix, Arizona,

109
00:05:41,215 --> 00:05:45,178
not for heroin or cocaine,
but for something just as dangerous.

110
00:05:45,261 --> 00:05:49,599
When it did become illegal, well,
how do you teach an old dog new tricks?

111
00:05:49,682 --> 00:05:52,393
You know, you just can't.
And he just kept doing it.

112
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:55,938
All the wrestlers used steroids.
Everybody across the board.

113
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:59,734
But for some reason,
with me, it's a different game.

114
00:05:59,817 --> 00:06:02,195
They're on a witch hunt.

115
00:06:02,278 --> 00:06:04,739
They're on a witch hunt.
They're after us all.

116
00:06:04,822 --> 00:06:07,909
They're after all of us.
They're after all of us.

117
00:06:07,992 --> 00:06:11,287
And I told him, "In life,
everybody's going to have speed bumps."

118
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:15,083
"Everybody's going to have speed bumps,
but you know what you've gotta do?"

119
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:16,959
"You gotta wear that seat belt, baby."

120
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:21,297
A doctor will go on trial
charged with prescribing anabolic steroids

121
00:06:21,381 --> 00:06:23,508
to several professional wrestlers,

122
00:06:23,591 --> 00:06:26,260
including the biggest name in the ring,
Hulk Hogan.

123
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:30,348
I went, "What the fuck?" Excuse me.
Didn't mean to say that. "What the heck?"

124
00:06:30,431 --> 00:06:33,643
We got the rug pulled out from under us.
The timing was bam, bam.

125
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,312
So I knew I had to do something.

126
00:06:37,271 --> 00:06:40,900
And I decided to go on Arsenio Hall
because he was a friend of mine.

127
00:06:40,983 --> 00:06:43,027
I actually got Arsenio Hall his job.

128
00:06:43,111 --> 00:06:46,030
So I said,
"Friendly fire. Let's give it a shot."

129
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:48,533
-You had been in the news.
-That's the problem.

130
00:06:48,616 --> 00:06:50,952
-People read the paper to be informed.
-Mm-hmm.

131
00:06:51,035 --> 00:06:53,079
Sometimes you read the paper,
and you get misinformed.

132
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:56,707
"Steroids, I never took a shot."

133
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:59,710
Basically, what I'd like to do is,
with all due respect,

134
00:06:59,794 --> 00:07:04,257
inform you and everybody else
that's misinformed by the newspapers.

135
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:06,342
Of course, I lied to him.

136
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:10,555
I'm not a steroid abuser,
and I do not use steroids.

137
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:15,852
All of us in the wrestling business,
we sat, and we went, "Jesus."

138
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:18,604
-I read the paper.
-The paper don't mean nothing.

139
00:07:18,688 --> 00:07:21,065
In a situation where it was unnecessary,

140
00:07:21,149 --> 00:07:22,525
he just completely lied.

141
00:07:22,608 --> 00:07:24,444
Everybody watching,

142
00:07:24,527 --> 00:07:28,656
with even, like, the most passing concept
of what steroids were, knew he was lying.

143
00:07:28,739 --> 00:07:31,534
It was just sad to see a hero doing that.

144
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:33,703
My name is David Shoemaker.

145
00:07:33,786 --> 00:07:36,414
I write columns about wrestling.

146
00:07:36,497 --> 00:07:39,584
I've been a huge fan of Hulk Hogan
since I was 6.

147
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:41,169
Almost my whole life.

148
00:07:41,252 --> 00:07:44,714
You had a whole generation
of little Hulksters training with you.

149
00:07:44,797 --> 00:07:47,467
Saying prayers with you, dude.
Eating their vitamins with you.

150
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:48,426
And you sold them out.

151
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:52,680
I understand why he did it.
You've got to keep up the image, you know.

152
00:07:52,763 --> 00:07:57,101
Like, Superman doesn't do steroids.
Superman is gifted with abilities, right?

153
00:07:57,185 --> 00:08:00,521
Hulk Hogan is like that.
He's a hero. He's a god.

154
00:08:00,605 --> 00:08:03,274
There are millions of kids
that believe in me and what I stand for.

155
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:06,736
Basically, it put a dark cloud
over everything that I believe in.

156
00:08:06,819 --> 00:08:11,699
But part of Hulkamania
also was being honest and forthright.

157
00:08:11,782 --> 00:08:13,326
Now we know you're lying.

158
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:15,369
So what else are you lying about?

159
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:17,914
It's the lie that gets you in the end.
It's like Nixon.

160
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:22,460
It's like, you know,
when you lie, you're a liar.

161
00:08:22,543 --> 00:08:25,963
We'll have to take it
to the Supreme Court of the Hulkamaniacs,

162
00:08:26,047 --> 00:08:27,590
the highest court in the land.

163
00:08:27,673 --> 00:08:30,218
I'm upset at him.
I don't like him as much now.

164
00:08:30,301 --> 00:08:32,303
There's a crescendo of opinion.

165
00:08:32,386 --> 00:08:36,140
What Hulk Hogan preaches
is apparently not what he practices.

166
00:08:36,224 --> 00:08:38,017
Congress ought to investigate.

167
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:41,229
What do you think
is gonna happen to Hulkamania?

168
00:08:41,312 --> 00:08:43,022
It's gonna die.

169
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:49,153
It's something that would be classified
in the "mistake" category.

170
00:08:49,237 --> 00:08:51,489
If I could relive it,
I wouldn't do it again.

171
00:08:51,572 --> 00:08:54,867
We have not been able
to reach Hogan for a response.

172
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:57,745
I was getting major heat
from the investigation.

173
00:08:57,828 --> 00:09:01,123
So it all just made sense
to move away from wrestling.

174
00:09:01,207 --> 00:09:03,042
I didn't have much of a choice.

175
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:06,754
I hope you have a good life
after you quit wrestling.

176
00:09:06,837 --> 00:09:09,674
I'm like, "Oh my God." You know?

177
00:09:09,757 --> 00:09:12,593
Hold on a minute,
you mean I can't be Hulk Hogan anymore?

178
00:09:14,178 --> 00:09:15,638
-Terry.
-Huh.

179
00:09:15,721 --> 00:09:17,932
Oh, no, he's got the gruels.

180
00:09:18,015 --> 00:09:19,475
Honey. What are you doing?

181
00:09:19,559 --> 00:09:25,356
We're putting
the Batcave Command Center together.

182
00:09:25,439 --> 00:09:26,315
Uh-huh.

183
00:09:26,399 --> 00:09:28,985
We have a swing trip door
behind the ground.

184
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:32,947
-Oh, that looks cool.
-Look at this watch.

185
00:09:33,531 --> 00:09:36,284
Hulk, for all I knew,
was never coming back.

186
00:09:41,789 --> 00:09:44,458
You gotta build somebody
to fill Hulk Hogan's shoes.

187
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:45,543
Pretty big shoes.

188
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:47,753
Who's going to be our next champion?

189
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:50,840
And it's, like, that guy.

190
00:09:50,923 --> 00:09:52,758
Bret "The Hitman" Hart.

191
00:09:56,929 --> 00:10:01,183
I was as stunned
and sort of blown away by that as anybody.

192
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:03,811
I was different than Hulk Hogan.

193
00:10:03,894 --> 00:10:07,398
Hulk Hogan was Elvis Presley.
I was the Robert De Niro of wrestling.

194
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:12,987
He's one of the absolute
best professional wrestlers of all time.

195
00:10:13,070 --> 00:10:16,282
Every Bret Hart match was a great match.

196
00:10:22,913 --> 00:10:27,668
The fans were ready to embrace him
and say, "This is the age of Bret Hart."

197
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:31,255
I always thought
that Hulk would be happy for me.

198
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:35,635
I said, "No, brother, it ain't happening."

199
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:42,475
Bret Hart isn't that feature film
that you thought you were going to see.

200
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:44,935
"The film wasn't as good
as I thought it was."

201
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:47,730
So I said,
"No, brother, you don't want that."

202
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:51,359
Hulk was now fishing about coming back.

203
00:10:51,442 --> 00:10:54,904
Hulk Hogan is not afraid to admit
he's made mistakes.

204
00:10:54,987 --> 00:10:57,365
On a personal level, I've made mistakes.

205
00:10:57,448 --> 00:11:00,117
On a business level,
I don't always make the right decisions.

206
00:11:00,201 --> 00:11:04,121
Hulk fucked up,
but I think Vince heard the pitch,

207
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:06,207
and Hulk Hogan was his Babe Ruth.

208
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:11,420
Hulkster, please tell us
what we want to hear. Come on!

209
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:14,632
I'm back in the WWE!

210
00:11:17,301 --> 00:11:20,763
Hogan had been gone.
Bret Hart is your champion.

211
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:22,390
And then Hogan comes back

212
00:11:22,473 --> 00:11:25,226
without the acknowledgement
of the steroid allegations.

213
00:11:25,309 --> 00:11:27,186
It just is a weird situation.

214
00:11:27,269 --> 00:11:30,356
In some ways, it felt like he was
either unwilling to change

215
00:11:30,439 --> 00:11:32,108
or unable to change.

216
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:34,985
I don't know what the plan was,

217
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:37,488
but it wasn't the right time
for him to come back.

218
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:44,203
It was announced Hulk Hogan would team
with his buddy, Brutus Beefcake,

219
00:11:44,286 --> 00:11:47,373
and challenge
for the Tag Team Championship

220
00:11:47,456 --> 00:11:49,208
at WrestleMania IX.

221
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:51,627
Make sure you get it all the way.

222
00:11:51,711 --> 00:11:54,088
There's no tag team
ever put together like this.

223
00:11:54,171 --> 00:11:56,257
Hulk Hogan. Brutus "the Barber" Beefcake.

224
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:59,009
Together, they are unstoppable!

225
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:02,221
That was supposed to be
Hulk Hogan's sole role.

226
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:04,473
Okay.

227
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:07,435
Hulk was always
at the top of the food chain.

228
00:12:07,518 --> 00:12:09,061
Everybody wants to keep that spot.

229
00:12:09,645 --> 00:12:11,355
So my uncle, Bret Hart.

230
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:14,734
The more successful Bret got,
the more he got in Hogan's lane.

231
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:17,111
All of a sudden,
it's like the claws come out.

232
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:21,741
I remember walking up to him
and said, "Hey, Terry."

233
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:25,995
I stood up with my hand out
to shake his hand for about 30 seconds.

234
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:28,956
He wouldn't look at me.
He kept talking to Beefcake.

235
00:12:29,039 --> 00:12:31,459
I can't imagine doing that intentionally.

236
00:12:31,542 --> 00:12:34,503
Maybe I had an off day.
Maybe I was drunk. Maybe I was high.

237
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:38,007
I don't know what to tell you,
but it wouldn't have been intentional.

238
00:12:38,966 --> 00:12:43,220
I knew right then and there, like,
I got the belt, and I got what he wants.

239
00:12:43,304 --> 00:12:45,014
I'm the enemy now.

240
00:12:45,097 --> 00:12:47,099
…comes a tall, handsome man

241
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:51,604
In a dusty black coat
With a red right hand

242
00:12:53,773 --> 00:12:56,192
I had that Hogan stroke back then.

243
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:58,694
Me and Vince were just bonded at the hip.

244
00:12:58,778 --> 00:13:01,739
I could pull the plug
on certain things or certain people.

245
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:05,868
Vince ultimately made the decision
for Hulk to win the title of Mania.

246
00:13:05,951 --> 00:13:06,786
Beautiful.

247
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:09,246
That day, I remember thinking,
"What a step backward."

248
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:14,001
It was a whole different audience,
and they were liking me, not Hulk Hogan.

249
00:13:14,084 --> 00:13:15,920
Bret got all up in my face
and got all rattled.

250
00:13:16,003 --> 00:13:18,714
I said, "What's with this guy?
I thought he was a team player."

251
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:23,052
I said to him, "It's going to backfire,
and it's going to be really bad."

252
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:26,347
Vince made the decision.
It's just one of those things.

253
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:27,890
Fuck you.

254
00:13:35,773 --> 00:13:39,610
Hulk came up with
such a phony, bullshit match.

255
00:13:39,693 --> 00:13:41,445
The kind of match Hulk would dream up.

256
00:13:43,906 --> 00:13:47,993
Bret Hart was wrestling
Dastardly Yokozuna.

257
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:51,872
Yokozuna's manager,
the inscrutable Mr. Fuji,

258
00:13:51,956 --> 00:13:58,212
throws some ceremonial salt
in Bret Hart's eyes.

259
00:13:59,421 --> 00:14:00,714
Bret is blinded…

260
00:14:03,008 --> 00:14:04,510
…and he's beaten for the title.

261
00:14:07,596 --> 00:14:09,056
But WrestleMania's not over yet.

262
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:14,728
-No!
-Hulk Hogan came out like the hero.

263
00:14:14,812 --> 00:14:17,940
The Hulk is concerned
with helping his friend Bret Hart.

264
00:14:18,023 --> 00:14:21,527
Yeah, he's my friend
coming out to run to my rescue.

265
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:23,153
"Go get him, Hulk."

266
00:14:23,237 --> 00:14:26,574
You know, "Go in there and win my belt."

267
00:14:26,657 --> 00:14:27,992
"Win it for me."

268
00:14:32,997 --> 00:14:34,373
It sucked.

269
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:39,253
People would be going, like,
"Why'd they do that to Bret Hart?"

270
00:14:40,254 --> 00:14:43,048
It was basically
this revolving-door gimmick

271
00:14:43,132 --> 00:14:46,677
to take the title off of Bret Hart
and put it back on Hulk Hogan.

272
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:51,682
And even as a kid, you know,
it just felt like Hogan was a bad friend.

273
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:54,685
He was a good guy once upon a time.

274
00:14:54,768 --> 00:14:58,731
But in the end, he was a backstabbing,
knife-wielding piece of shit.

275
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:07,948
People might have been getting
a little weary of Hogan to begin with.

276
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:11,619
This is not 1985 anymore.

277
00:15:12,369 --> 00:15:15,497
The Hulk's shtick
was starting to wear pretty thin.

278
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:18,667
It was the same match
every night for six, seven years.

279
00:15:18,751 --> 00:15:22,046
And people were getting tired
of the leg drop

280
00:15:22,129 --> 00:15:26,258
and, uh, you know,
the milking the crowd and the Hulking up.

281
00:15:26,342 --> 00:15:28,469
The truth is, it had passed.

282
00:15:28,552 --> 00:15:31,597
I don't wanna say he was a one-trick pony,
but you'd seen it.

283
00:15:32,389 --> 00:15:35,809
It wasn't drawing anymore.
People had moved on.

284
00:15:38,562 --> 00:15:41,732
And Vince would always do
what was best for business.

285
00:15:41,815 --> 00:15:44,443
Ladies and gentlemen,
my good friend, my boss,

286
00:15:44,526 --> 00:15:47,655
and the toughest dude I've ever been
in the ring with, Vince McMahon.

287
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:49,365
Hogan, I'm sure, believed

288
00:15:49,448 --> 00:15:52,201
he was not only the reason
for WWE's success,

289
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:54,328
but he had a lot left in the tank.

290
00:15:54,411 --> 00:15:57,164
I thought I might be able
to keep climbing that ladder

291
00:15:57,247 --> 00:15:58,707
with the support of the machine.

292
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:02,711
And when I asked Vince what's next,

293
00:16:02,795 --> 00:16:05,172
he goes, "I think your run's about over."

294
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:08,926
He said, "The red and yellow is dead."

295
00:16:09,009 --> 00:16:12,262
And I wasn't going to get
a push there anymore.

296
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:16,225
Hulk said, "We might have a major problem
starting to happen. I talked to Vince."

297
00:16:16,308 --> 00:16:19,812
I said, "What happened?"
He told me. I went, "Oh my God."

298
00:16:20,938 --> 00:16:25,401
For me, it was the classic Vince McMahon,
in my opinion, mistake.

299
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:29,113
Baby, don't understand

300
00:16:29,196 --> 00:16:33,033
Why we can't just hold on
To each other's hands…

301
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:36,370
He may know what he knows
on how to run a huge company

302
00:16:36,453 --> 00:16:38,664
ten times, a million times better than me.

303
00:16:38,747 --> 00:16:42,751
But as far as my character
and what I know about my brand and name,

304
00:16:42,835 --> 00:16:44,128
I thought he was way off.

305
00:16:44,211 --> 00:16:49,008
This time might be the last, I fear

306
00:16:49,091 --> 00:16:50,467
Unless I…

307
00:16:50,551 --> 00:16:52,011
We had our differences.

308
00:16:52,928 --> 00:16:56,598
And Hogan's ego, on occasion,
would get out of line.

309
00:16:56,682 --> 00:16:58,851
It took two to build an empire.

310
00:16:58,934 --> 00:17:01,061
I felt we were close personally.

311
00:17:01,145 --> 00:17:02,813
But for him,

312
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:07,484
the personal stuff
was actually a business front.

313
00:17:07,568 --> 00:17:10,195
And in so many words, he said that to me.

314
00:17:12,823 --> 00:17:15,159
So I made a decision
that nobody's gonna hurt me again.

315
00:17:18,328 --> 00:17:21,582
So take these broken wings

316
00:17:21,665 --> 00:17:23,584
And learn to fly again…

317
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:24,710
Vince called me,

318
00:17:24,793 --> 00:17:27,546
and I went on a rant
because I was so mad at him.

319
00:17:27,629 --> 00:17:30,466
He said, "We'll find out who's stronger."

320
00:17:30,549 --> 00:17:33,177
"The machine behind me or me."

321
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:35,637
I just went nuts. You name it.

322
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:41,143
Every… bad name that you could say
that would get you canceled.

323
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:42,061
You know?

324
00:17:42,144 --> 00:17:45,272
-He's in a bad spot now.
-In a very bad situation.

325
00:17:45,355 --> 00:17:48,317
Hulk was unhappy. Vince was unhappy.

326
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:50,194
It was really tough to watch.

327
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:55,324
Vince drew a line and said,
"You'll never work here again."

328
00:17:55,407 --> 00:17:58,285
He's going to bomb Hulkamania!

329
00:17:58,368 --> 00:17:59,870
I'm good at getting fired.

330
00:18:00,788 --> 00:18:03,082
Hulkamania is dead.

331
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:06,210
Children crying.
This is an emotional moment.

332
00:18:06,293 --> 00:18:09,963
The heart of America,
Hulk Hogan, has just stopped beating.

333
00:18:10,047 --> 00:18:14,093
And when we hear the voices sing

334
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:20,432
You got to learn to fly
Learn to live, to love so free

335
00:18:20,516 --> 00:18:22,935
It was sad. It was sad.

336
00:18:23,018 --> 00:18:26,188
But I think Hulk saw it as an opportunity

337
00:18:26,271 --> 00:18:30,442
to, to get away
and make himself worth more.

338
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:35,030
Should I say "Mr. Hogan"?
Maybe "Hulky"? Is that too familiar?

339
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:36,490
"Muscles" is an option, I suppose.

340
00:18:36,573 --> 00:18:38,992
Although that was
the name of Michael Jackson's snake.

341
00:18:39,076 --> 00:18:42,204
He sometimes likes "Hulkster,"
but that sounds ridiculous.

342
00:18:42,287 --> 00:18:43,539
Hulk, H-H.

343
00:18:43,622 --> 00:18:44,957
-Hulkster.
-The Hulkster.

344
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:47,960
-The Hulkster.
-Um… now, you're making movies now.

345
00:18:48,043 --> 00:18:49,211
Yes, sir.

346
00:18:49,294 --> 00:18:52,214
You've moved on from wrestling,
and you're making movies.

347
00:18:52,297 --> 00:18:55,717
Basically, I want to work. I'm too young
to sit in a rocking chair with my kids.

348
00:18:55,801 --> 00:18:59,888
I don't want my kids to think Daddy eats
peanut butter sandwiches and watches TV.

349
00:18:59,972 --> 00:19:02,391
So, the people
in the film industry said, "Wow."

350
00:19:02,474 --> 00:19:06,145
"This guy can walk, chew bubblegum,
talk, and maybe he's articulate too."

351
00:19:14,444 --> 00:19:15,696
Outside of wrestling,

352
00:19:15,779 --> 00:19:19,116
Hulk was really the first person
to transcend WWE.

353
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:24,288
Doing movies and TV shows and commercials.

354
00:19:24,371 --> 00:19:29,168
A true artiste should be remembered
for his inspiration, not his perspiration.

355
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:33,463
You know, mingling with Hollywood.

356
00:19:34,464 --> 00:19:36,800
Suburban Commando.

357
00:19:37,467 --> 00:19:40,095
The Hulkster is Shep…

358
00:19:40,179 --> 00:19:41,180
Whoop!

359
00:19:41,263 --> 00:19:42,181
…Ramsey.

360
00:19:42,264 --> 00:19:46,143
A valiant galactic warrior
stranded on Earth.

361
00:19:46,226 --> 00:19:49,688
-I'm here to rent the apartment.
-Honey, it's for you.

362
00:19:49,771 --> 00:19:54,443
At first, I was intimidated.
You know, I didn't want to piss him off.

363
00:19:54,526 --> 00:19:58,322
That physique and the build and his face…

364
00:19:58,405 --> 00:20:00,490
He looked like he was from outer space.

365
00:20:00,574 --> 00:20:03,869
How the hell was I supposed to know
you were some sort of alien Rambo?

366
00:20:03,952 --> 00:20:06,622
But he wasn't scary as a person.

367
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:08,290
He was just so friendly.

368
00:20:08,373 --> 00:20:10,667
He was a friend right away.

369
00:20:10,751 --> 00:20:14,046
And the crossover to film,
that's helped me so much.

370
00:20:14,129 --> 00:20:17,132
I just need people around me
like Christopher Lloyd and Shelley Duvall

371
00:20:17,216 --> 00:20:18,467
to make sure I'm on the mark.

372
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:21,178
Take off the bandana,
wash the old bald head.

373
00:20:21,261 --> 00:20:24,306
The wife holds the iron fist,
and I play Mr. Nanny at home.

374
00:20:24,389 --> 00:20:25,390
Sing.

375
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:28,268
Twinkle, twinkle, little star

376
00:20:28,352 --> 00:20:32,940
I never pictured myself as a movie star
because I can look in the mirror.

377
00:20:33,023 --> 00:20:38,028
It's not Brad Pitt staring at you
across the mirror or Sean Connery.

378
00:20:41,198 --> 00:20:42,574
You're bigger than most trees.

379
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:44,243
My cat.

380
00:20:46,954 --> 00:20:49,748
Even if you didn't know
or watch wrestling,

381
00:20:49,831 --> 00:20:53,752
or you didn't know what WWE was,
you knew that he was a star.

382
00:20:54,336 --> 00:20:57,339
Gremlins? In this theater? Now?

383
00:20:57,422 --> 00:20:58,966
What a departure for you.

384
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:01,927
-The poster has you wearing a tutu.
-A tutu?

385
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:03,971
But this cross-dressing,
this wearing this tutu,

386
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:07,599
is this something you did for the film,
or have you done this privately?

387
00:21:07,683 --> 00:21:09,476
You look positively effervescent.

388
00:21:09,559 --> 00:21:11,395
May I offer you tea?

389
00:21:11,478 --> 00:21:14,731
He wasn't going to be
going out and doing King Lear.

390
00:21:14,815 --> 00:21:16,149
That was not his ambition.

391
00:21:17,359 --> 00:21:19,278
The media killed me.

392
00:21:19,361 --> 00:21:23,573
My face is so much like a character,
a cartoon character.

393
00:21:23,657 --> 00:21:26,785
As soon as I open up my eyebrows,
bam, the whole screen blows.

394
00:21:26,868 --> 00:21:30,872
People who watch Hulk Hogan on television
and kids who have the Hogan character,

395
00:21:30,956 --> 00:21:32,291
and they see this movie,

396
00:21:32,374 --> 00:21:35,002
are just going to be offended
and disappointed in it.

397
00:21:35,085 --> 00:21:38,588
I already heard about one 12-year-old girl
who walked out midway.

398
00:21:38,672 --> 00:21:42,384
You have to be very bad
to get a child to leave the theater.

399
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:43,844
Whatever.

400
00:21:43,927 --> 00:21:48,140
I was cool with it, man.
I knew I was a wrestler, just scamming by.

401
00:21:49,141 --> 00:21:51,184
You mentioned
you were shooting in Florida.

402
00:21:51,268 --> 00:21:53,103
You're originally from Florida, right?

403
00:21:53,186 --> 00:21:55,188
-Yes.
-I thought you were.

404
00:21:55,272 --> 00:21:57,607
-I spent a lot of time in the swamps.
-In the swamps?

405
00:21:57,691 --> 00:21:59,401
Thunder in Paradise.

406
00:21:59,484 --> 00:22:02,863
He was filming locally
with these really awesome boats.

407
00:22:03,697 --> 00:22:06,450
It was almost like, um,
Baywatch, but cooler.

408
00:22:09,077 --> 00:22:11,455
We'd get to spend time with him on set.

409
00:22:11,538 --> 00:22:13,290
Well, when I was wrestling,

410
00:22:13,373 --> 00:22:16,668
I was on the road
and gone more than I was home.

411
00:22:16,752 --> 00:22:19,129
I started making more movies.

412
00:22:19,212 --> 00:22:20,964
I was home with the kids.

413
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:24,718
He loved spending more time at home.
It felt good. It felt nice.

414
00:22:28,388 --> 00:22:29,973
-Are you happy?
-Yeah.

415
00:22:30,057 --> 00:22:32,809
He'd pack their lunches.
He'd beat me to the kitchen.

416
00:22:32,893 --> 00:22:35,354
I'm like, "You didn't have to, babe."
He's like, "I wanted to."

417
00:22:35,437 --> 00:22:38,315
He liked figuring out
what to put in their lunch pails.

418
00:22:38,398 --> 00:22:39,358
It was new to him.

419
00:22:39,441 --> 00:22:41,401
Your dad made him
a peanut butter and jelly sandwich.

420
00:22:41,485 --> 00:22:43,528
I love you very much.

421
00:22:43,612 --> 00:22:47,074
-Love you too.
-I love you very much, poop.

422
00:22:47,741 --> 00:22:50,494
Do you love me?

423
00:22:50,577 --> 00:22:54,122
And we have the star of our show,
Thunder in Paradise,

424
00:22:54,206 --> 00:22:56,917
Hulk Hogan, with his son, Nicky.

425
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:59,586
I'll take you to the entrance.
That's very close.

426
00:22:59,669 --> 00:23:01,004
Out he goes. Good luck.

427
00:23:01,088 --> 00:23:04,925
I was making these movies
but didn't have my heart all the way in.

428
00:23:06,676 --> 00:23:09,805
I have a hard time
sitting around for 14 hours a day,

429
00:23:09,888 --> 00:23:13,225
waiting for the 1st AD to get me
for three minutes.

430
00:23:14,184 --> 00:23:17,187
I didn't like the process

431
00:23:17,270 --> 00:23:19,314
because I was so spoiled with wrestling.

432
00:23:19,398 --> 00:23:24,027
Wrestling for 10 or 15 minutes
and making the "million-dollar minimum."

433
00:23:24,111 --> 00:23:27,364
When he got up in the ring,
he was a showman.

434
00:23:27,447 --> 00:23:29,658
He wanted to share his pleasure.

435
00:23:29,741 --> 00:23:31,493
Crowds yelling and screaming.

436
00:23:33,078 --> 00:23:34,788
The acting, it was kind of a lark,

437
00:23:34,871 --> 00:23:37,290
but I don't think
it mattered to him that much.

438
00:23:37,374 --> 00:23:42,129
I'd love to climb back in there once more,
maybe have Kermit as my business manager.

439
00:23:42,212 --> 00:23:44,965
I'd love to. I've never been
in a wrestling ring before.

440
00:23:45,048 --> 00:23:46,091
I started going squirrelly.

441
00:23:46,174 --> 00:23:47,843
Take some beach towels.

442
00:23:47,926 --> 00:23:51,012
I said, "I appreciate
becoming the next John Wayne,

443
00:23:51,096 --> 00:23:54,099
but I gotta get out of here.
This is driving me crazy."

444
00:23:54,182 --> 00:23:56,226
-Cut!
-Cut it. Print it.

445
00:23:56,309 --> 00:23:57,644
I'll go back to wrestling.

446
00:23:59,855 --> 00:24:02,023
Pull me up! Pull me up.

447
00:24:03,316 --> 00:24:04,151
Come on.

448
00:24:04,234 --> 00:24:08,155
You know and I know there could be
a possible return to the ring, Hulkster.

449
00:24:08,238 --> 00:24:11,074
You know something, brother,
I was in the airport last night.

450
00:24:11,158 --> 00:24:14,744
When I flew here to see Regis,
a little old lady came up to me and goes,

451
00:24:14,828 --> 00:24:17,664
"Hulk Hogan,
you make me feel 18 years old again."

452
00:24:17,747 --> 00:24:20,792
She said, "I quit watching wrestling
when you weren't on there."

453
00:24:20,876 --> 00:24:23,044
"You were the greatest there ever was,
ever will be."

454
00:24:23,128 --> 00:24:24,546
"It's not the same without you."

455
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:37,225
So, we were at Disney Studios,
and our soundstage for Thunder in Paradise

456
00:24:37,309 --> 00:24:41,605
was right next to the wrestling soundstage
for the WCW wrestling.

457
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:46,902
Ow!

458
00:24:50,197 --> 00:24:54,451
WCW wasn't sports entertainment,
it was "wrestling."

459
00:24:54,534 --> 00:24:57,078
Eye for an eye,
tooth for a tooth "wrestling."

460
00:24:57,162 --> 00:25:00,582
I'm bringing the rope in.
They can say I can't spit tobacco.

461
00:25:00,665 --> 00:25:02,459
They can say everything they want!

462
00:25:02,542 --> 00:25:04,920
It was a real distant,

463
00:25:05,003 --> 00:25:08,798
real distant number two
from what the WWE was.

464
00:25:08,882 --> 00:25:10,300
It was rough.

465
00:25:11,009 --> 00:25:16,681
From the Pacific Northwest, Big Josh!

466
00:25:17,432 --> 00:25:19,643
WCW had never turned a dollar of profit

467
00:25:19,726 --> 00:25:22,103
and was losing
millions of dollars every year.

468
00:25:22,187 --> 00:25:24,064
Here comes Robocop, Bob!

469
00:25:24,147 --> 00:25:27,984
Our idea of a good turnout
in an arena was like 1,200 people.

470
00:25:28,068 --> 00:25:29,653
He pulled that door off!

471
00:25:29,736 --> 00:25:31,821
Especially if half of them were sober.

472
00:25:31,905 --> 00:25:33,448
What strength by Robocop!

473
00:25:39,538 --> 00:25:43,166
My primary goal
was to convince advertisers and sponsors

474
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:44,501
that we were legitimate.

475
00:25:44,584 --> 00:25:47,837
And now he sticks his head
into that watering trough!

476
00:25:47,921 --> 00:25:52,759
Because WCW was perceived to be
just a notch or two above porn,

477
00:25:53,426 --> 00:25:58,682
I needed Madison Avenue
to look at WCW as a competitor to WWE.

478
00:26:02,310 --> 00:26:03,979
And I needed Hogan to do that.

479
00:26:04,896 --> 00:26:07,899
I knew Hulk was on the lot,
we're on the lot,

480
00:26:07,983 --> 00:26:10,402
and I took advantage
to get a meeting with Hulk.

481
00:26:10,485 --> 00:26:13,572
He comes approaching me
and asked me if I'd come to work for him.

482
00:26:14,197 --> 00:26:15,824
I said, "Let me think about it."

483
00:26:15,907 --> 00:26:18,201
Happy New Year.

484
00:26:18,285 --> 00:26:21,329
And then
he looked at me one day, and he's like,

485
00:26:21,413 --> 00:26:23,415
"Well, are you ready to do another run?"

486
00:26:23,498 --> 00:26:24,916
Happy New Year!

487
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:27,127
I thought he'd be home
a little bit longer,

488
00:26:27,210 --> 00:26:30,255
but, you know, work was a-calling.

489
00:26:31,131 --> 00:26:35,218
And, uh, '94 will be better
than '92 and '93 for sure.

490
00:26:35,302 --> 00:26:38,388
Yeah, honey. Love you.

491
00:26:38,471 --> 00:26:41,850
By the time I'd cut my deal,
it was ridiculous.

492
00:26:41,933 --> 00:26:43,852
I got the money.

493
00:26:43,935 --> 00:26:45,979
We got the money

494
00:26:46,062 --> 00:26:49,899
I had to actually give back
some of the deal that I did

495
00:26:49,983 --> 00:26:52,444
so that certain people
would not get fired.

496
00:26:56,281 --> 00:26:58,366
And money, we had a lot of money.

497
00:26:58,450 --> 00:27:01,328
It didn't matter
if he slowed down or sped up.

498
00:27:01,411 --> 00:27:04,706
It was… We were comfortable.
But he never wanted to retire.

499
00:27:04,789 --> 00:27:06,791
He was just addicted to the ring.

500
00:27:06,875 --> 00:27:11,212
Did you ever think, at age 40,
this would be kind of a comeback for you?

501
00:27:11,296 --> 00:27:14,924
Yeah, well, you know,
this is kind of like 40 going on 18.

502
00:27:17,302 --> 00:27:19,971
Who do you want to see in WCW?

503
00:27:20,055 --> 00:27:21,640
Hulk Hogan!

504
00:27:21,723 --> 00:27:24,142
Hulk Hogan knew he had value in his brand.

505
00:27:24,225 --> 00:27:28,563
The single most popular wrestling star
in the history of the sport here.

506
00:27:28,647 --> 00:27:31,232
He told me
I could run the company any way I wanted.

507
00:27:31,316 --> 00:27:33,526
I could take over and run the company.

508
00:27:33,610 --> 00:27:36,321
He said, "Promise me
you'll put lightning in a bottle."

509
00:27:36,404 --> 00:27:37,822
I said, "No problem at all."

510
00:27:37,906 --> 00:27:42,369
By the early '90s,
there was no denying the fact

511
00:27:42,452 --> 00:27:45,622
that the Hulkamania machine
was winding down.

512
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:51,836
He comes to WCW, and they have
a more prehistoric version of Hulk Hogan.

513
00:27:52,545 --> 00:27:57,342
This is the greatest day
that professional wrestling has ever seen.

514
00:27:57,425 --> 00:28:02,347
There is this incredibly staged parade,
where he's in this red Corvette.

515
00:28:02,430 --> 00:28:04,391
There are fake reporters.

516
00:28:04,474 --> 00:28:06,226
There is a fake audience.

517
00:28:06,309 --> 00:28:09,354
Look at the faces of the kids
and the excitement.

518
00:28:09,437 --> 00:28:12,065
That's what they wanted,
to see Hogan back,

519
00:28:12,148 --> 00:28:13,400
and that's what they got.

520
00:28:13,483 --> 00:28:16,111
Like The Babe in the town,
like Henry Aaron.

521
00:28:16,194 --> 00:28:19,197
WCW was leaning into the nostalgia.

522
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:20,407
We're in a new era now.

523
00:28:20,490 --> 00:28:24,369
"So why are you the only people
that don't see this?" You know?

524
00:28:24,869 --> 00:28:25,787
Oh, hi.

525
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:27,288
People compare this move

526
00:28:27,372 --> 00:28:29,791
to Joe Montana's
from the 49ers to the Chiefs.

527
00:28:29,874 --> 00:28:33,086
-What do you think about that?
-You know something, brother?

528
00:28:33,169 --> 00:28:35,296
The big man upstairs, he moves mountains.

529
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:38,967
In seven days and seven nights,
he created the heaven and the Earth.

530
00:28:39,050 --> 00:28:42,220
And on the eighth day, dude,
he created Hulkamania.

531
00:28:42,303 --> 00:28:45,306
So I can't wait to come into the WCW

532
00:28:45,390 --> 00:28:48,268
and show them
what the strongest force is all about.

533
00:28:50,729 --> 00:28:55,150
Hulk Hogan in WCW
I don't think had the impact

534
00:28:55,233 --> 00:28:57,277
it would have had a few years earlier.

535
00:28:57,360 --> 00:29:01,698
Particularly in the wake
of the steroid scandal,

536
00:29:01,781 --> 00:29:03,491
which wasn't over.

537
00:29:03,575 --> 00:29:06,161
The Feds accused this man, Vince McMahon,

538
00:29:06,244 --> 00:29:08,955
of pumping his stable of stars
with steroids.

539
00:29:09,038 --> 00:29:14,586
The federal government contended
that Vince was a steroid dealer.

540
00:29:14,669 --> 00:29:16,337
Vince got indicted.

541
00:29:16,421 --> 00:29:19,716
I was subpoenaed
to be the star witness for the Feds.

542
00:29:19,799 --> 00:29:22,260
If the Feds
pin Mr. McMahon with a conviction,

543
00:29:22,343 --> 00:29:24,095
he could face 11 years in jail.

544
00:29:24,179 --> 00:29:28,975
It was the anticipation
that Hulk Hogan would get up on the stand

545
00:29:29,058 --> 00:29:33,188
and reveal secrets about Vince McMahon
no one had ever heard before.

546
00:29:33,271 --> 00:29:37,192
They wanted me to say
that Vince sold me steroids.

547
00:29:37,275 --> 00:29:40,945
I wanted to move on. Shut this crap down
that was still going on.

548
00:29:41,029 --> 00:29:43,198
So I went in the federal courtroom.

549
00:29:43,281 --> 00:29:44,824
I told the truth.

550
00:29:44,908 --> 00:29:47,994
Defense, "Do you recall
Mr. McMahon handing you steroids?"

551
00:29:48,077 --> 00:29:49,329
Hulk replied, "Never."

552
00:29:49,412 --> 00:29:51,372
I said he never sold me steroids.

553
00:29:51,456 --> 00:29:54,375
I told the judge
it was just a carton of cigarettes.

554
00:29:54,459 --> 00:29:58,213
"Give me a carton of cigarettes.
I'll pay you back." Just like that.

555
00:29:58,296 --> 00:30:01,174
"Sometimes my steroids
were sent to the office,

556
00:30:01,257 --> 00:30:03,718
and I picked it up with my fan mail."

557
00:30:03,802 --> 00:30:06,304
He said yes, he took them, finally,

558
00:30:06,387 --> 00:30:08,515
and said yes, it was of his own volition.

559
00:30:08,598 --> 00:30:11,559
A former wrestler
admitted publicly for the first time

560
00:30:11,643 --> 00:30:14,270
that he used steroids for 13 years.

561
00:30:14,354 --> 00:30:16,189
He basically sunk their case.

562
00:30:16,272 --> 00:30:20,193
After 2 days of deliberations,
the verdict, not guilty.

563
00:30:20,276 --> 00:30:23,154
Hulk's testimony
definitely helped WWE's case.

564
00:30:23,238 --> 00:30:25,281
Then the next thing you know,

565
00:30:25,365 --> 00:30:27,909
on the courtroom steps,
the media hit Vince.

566
00:30:27,992 --> 00:30:30,954
Did you feel badly
Hogan testified against you?

567
00:30:31,037 --> 00:30:36,042
Yes, when it's really tough to have
someone with whom you've worked with

568
00:30:36,125 --> 00:30:41,047
to, uh, to take the stand
and tell certainly not the whole truth.

569
00:30:41,130 --> 00:30:46,761
It looks like some kind of wrestling promo
that Vince cut outside the courthouse.

570
00:30:46,845 --> 00:30:50,890
And it just blew me away
that he'd say that when I saved his ass.

571
00:30:50,974 --> 00:30:53,601
We say in the WWE,
and it could very well be,

572
00:30:53,685 --> 00:30:57,272
that the hunters soon will be the hunted.

573
00:30:57,355 --> 00:30:58,857
Oh, really?

574
00:30:58,940 --> 00:31:01,609
You know, you really want me
to tell the truth? Okay.

575
00:31:01,693 --> 00:31:03,570
I know where the bodies are buried.

576
00:31:03,653 --> 00:31:08,658
If it had been a day for vengeance,
I guess he would be getting out about now,

577
00:31:08,741 --> 00:31:11,369
and I'd be owning the wrestling business.

578
00:31:11,452 --> 00:31:15,081
Clearly, there was
personal animosity between these guys.

579
00:31:15,164 --> 00:31:18,751
Hogan had already left the company
to work for the competition.

580
00:31:18,835 --> 00:31:20,628
Mr. McMahon is the winner.

581
00:31:20,712 --> 00:31:23,423
Oh, man,
I couldn't wait to get down to WCW

582
00:31:23,506 --> 00:31:24,799
and win that World Title.

583
00:31:24,883 --> 00:31:27,343
Teach everybody a lesson
about who the man was.

584
00:31:27,427 --> 00:31:30,096
Outside court, Hulk was tamer than usual.

585
00:31:30,179 --> 00:31:31,848
Did Vince give you steroids?

586
00:31:31,931 --> 00:31:35,518
The only thing Hulk said,
"Watch my pay-per-view special."

587
00:31:35,602 --> 00:31:41,900
He's American made

588
00:31:44,277 --> 00:31:47,655
He's back! He's back!

589
00:31:48,615 --> 00:31:53,828
He's got the red white and blue
Running through his veins

590
00:31:56,539 --> 00:32:01,753
He was born and raised
In the U.S. of A

591
00:32:01,836 --> 00:32:03,463
After the steroid trial,

592
00:32:03,546 --> 00:32:08,134
I believe I got that respect
that I had lost back.

593
00:32:08,217 --> 00:32:10,470
The Hulkster is in the ring!

594
00:32:10,553 --> 00:32:12,764
It seemed like a real good night.

595
00:32:12,847 --> 00:32:14,265
My run wasn't over.

596
00:32:14,349 --> 00:32:16,935
Vince apparently was wrong.
I was still hot.

597
00:32:17,018 --> 00:32:18,728
American

598
00:32:18,811 --> 00:32:21,189
The Hulkster throws him on the buckle!

599
00:32:21,272 --> 00:32:22,857
American

600
00:32:22,941 --> 00:32:26,444
Down goes Flair.
Hulkster never looked better.

601
00:32:27,028 --> 00:32:29,614
I never thought
I'd see him back in the ring.

602
00:32:29,697 --> 00:32:31,908
The Hulkster looks tremendous!

603
00:32:31,991 --> 00:32:33,451
Great shape!

604
00:32:33,534 --> 00:32:35,870
Whoa! Did he drill him!

605
00:32:37,956 --> 00:32:41,125
I don't mean to be mean,
but I do remember watching that match

606
00:32:41,209 --> 00:32:44,379
and thinking
that this was an older Hulk Hogan.

607
00:32:44,462 --> 00:32:47,966
Come on,
squeeze that mustache right off his face!

608
00:32:48,049 --> 00:32:51,552
It was not the same Hogan
that body-slammed Andre the Giant.

609
00:32:51,636 --> 00:32:54,806
By no means. It felt like it was
more of the winter of his career.

610
00:32:58,226 --> 00:32:59,769
Come on, baby.

611
00:32:59,852 --> 00:33:02,480
It was just very tired to me.

612
00:33:02,563 --> 00:33:04,440
As a kid, I'm like,
"What's wrong with him?"

613
00:33:04,524 --> 00:33:07,610
"He's not the muscle-bound hero
he used to be."

614
00:33:07,694 --> 00:33:10,405
Three!

615
00:33:10,488 --> 00:33:12,240
The good old days are back,

616
00:33:12,323 --> 00:33:15,493
and believe me, Hulk Hogan,
congratulations.

617
00:33:15,576 --> 00:33:18,079
You have done it again, my friend.
What a day!

618
00:33:18,162 --> 00:33:21,374
Hulkster still rules! Whoo!

619
00:33:21,457 --> 00:33:22,500
All right!

620
00:33:22,583 --> 00:33:26,546
The first three or four months
when Hogan arrived,

621
00:33:26,629 --> 00:33:28,339
everybody was still so excited.

622
00:33:28,423 --> 00:33:30,341
It was still… It's Hulk Hogan.

623
00:33:31,134 --> 00:33:33,928
But all of a sudden, you started hearing

624
00:33:35,138 --> 00:33:36,639
more boos.

625
00:33:39,934 --> 00:33:41,352
Oh, really?

626
00:33:41,436 --> 00:33:43,354
So you want to boo me?

627
00:33:43,438 --> 00:33:44,355
Your hero?

628
00:33:44,439 --> 00:33:46,024
Well, you know what?

629
00:33:46,107 --> 00:33:47,734
What goes around comes around.

630
00:33:47,817 --> 00:33:50,069
And there were signs out there.

631
00:33:50,153 --> 00:33:52,864
I didn't bang on too much,
but I did see them.

632
00:33:52,947 --> 00:33:55,658
-Negative signs out there.
-What did they say?

633
00:33:55,742 --> 00:33:58,327
They said,
"Did you take your shot today?" Whatever.

634
00:33:58,411 --> 00:34:02,874
Some smart-ass thing from some fans
that were trying to rile me up.

635
00:34:02,957 --> 00:34:05,168
For such a long time,
people went crazy over him.

636
00:34:05,251 --> 00:34:08,588
All of a sudden, he started to get
more boos, more boos. You know?

637
00:34:08,671 --> 00:34:11,090
One night they love you,
one night they don't.

638
00:34:11,841 --> 00:34:13,176
I know it hurt Hulk.

639
00:34:13,259 --> 00:34:17,013
If you do that character for so long…
That's who Hulk Hogan is, you know?

640
00:34:17,096 --> 00:34:18,681
He was just that person.

641
00:34:18,765 --> 00:34:22,477
He would get up,
take a shower, have his coffee.

642
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:24,979
-I've got shit to do.
-Like what?

643
00:34:25,063 --> 00:34:27,899
Find the stuff I'll need
for four days and for interviews

644
00:34:27,982 --> 00:34:29,609
and get my headbands washed.

645
00:34:29,692 --> 00:34:32,612
Throw down what you need.
I'll be in in about 20 minutes.

646
00:34:32,695 --> 00:34:35,656
All of a sudden,
it would just be like, "Woo."

647
00:34:36,741 --> 00:34:38,493
All of a sudden, he was Hulk.

648
00:34:38,576 --> 00:34:40,828
Look what I'm married to.

649
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:42,330
Yeah, yeah.

650
00:34:43,956 --> 00:34:46,167
Come on. Go ahead and smile. You love it.

651
00:34:46,250 --> 00:34:48,127
I wasn't happy.

652
00:34:48,211 --> 00:34:50,838
I was out of it.
I didn't know what I was doing.

653
00:34:50,922 --> 00:34:52,548
Didn't know who I was anymore.

654
00:34:52,632 --> 00:34:54,217
Can I see the blue eyes?

655
00:34:54,300 --> 00:35:01,057
It was the end of an era
where you could have pure good guys.

656
00:35:01,140 --> 00:35:04,393
And that character
had just run its course with the audience

657
00:35:04,477 --> 00:35:07,480
because they were seeing
other cooler stuff.

658
00:35:07,563 --> 00:35:10,024
We're going absolutely nowhere.

659
00:35:10,108 --> 00:35:11,484
We do, however, have--

660
00:35:11,567 --> 00:35:13,319
-Wait a minute.
-What?

661
00:35:13,402 --> 00:35:14,654
Now look at this.

662
00:35:21,869 --> 00:35:25,706
that since I was seven years old,
I wanted to wrestle.

663
00:35:25,790 --> 00:35:28,459
I watched this as a kid.
I thought it was fake as shit.

664
00:35:28,543 --> 00:35:30,211
We got a ticket.

665
00:35:32,046 --> 00:35:34,257
Came to see the big boys!

666
00:35:34,340 --> 00:35:38,177
The reason I got in this business,
because I saw Hulk.

667
00:35:39,178 --> 00:35:41,347
I thought,
"I'm a better athlete than him."

668
00:35:41,430 --> 00:35:42,640
"I look better than him."

669
00:35:42,723 --> 00:35:45,393
"If he can fucking do this
and make that money, I can."

670
00:35:45,476 --> 00:35:49,605
They moved him outside.
They've got baseball bats in their hands.

671
00:35:49,689 --> 00:35:53,025
Ladies and gentlemen, never have we seen
or witnessed anything like this.

672
00:35:53,109 --> 00:35:55,236
There won't be a hostile takeover of WCW.

673
00:35:55,319 --> 00:35:57,822
You can't walk in and say you run things.

674
00:35:57,905 --> 00:36:02,118
There has never been a wrestling storyline

675
00:36:02,201 --> 00:36:05,288
that has come close to the nWo

676
00:36:05,371 --> 00:36:08,374
because it blurred the lines
between what's real and not.

677
00:36:09,542 --> 00:36:11,127
It was two guys,

678
00:36:11,210 --> 00:36:12,170
Kevin Nash,

679
00:36:12,253 --> 00:36:13,171
Scott Hall,

680
00:36:13,254 --> 00:36:15,590
both of whom
had previously worked for WCW.

681
00:36:17,008 --> 00:36:19,594
Because they felt like
they were disrespected,

682
00:36:21,053 --> 00:36:23,347
they go to WWE, they become huge stars.

683
00:36:23,431 --> 00:36:26,184
Say hello to Razor Ramon.

684
00:36:26,267 --> 00:36:30,563
So big that they decided
to come back to WCW

685
00:36:30,646 --> 00:36:32,648
and make everybody pay.

686
00:36:32,732 --> 00:36:35,276
Yeah, where's Hogan? Where's Hogan?

687
00:36:35,359 --> 00:36:38,654
Out doing another episode
of Blunder in Paradise?

688
00:36:38,738 --> 00:36:40,948
I went, "Oh, wow."

689
00:36:41,032 --> 00:36:42,867
"This is really interesting."

690
00:36:42,950 --> 00:36:46,662
"This looks like somebody jumped the fence
and got in through the back door."

691
00:36:46,746 --> 00:36:49,749
"This looks real. And they're coming in."

692
00:36:49,832 --> 00:36:51,792
Oh, for cr-- Whoa.

693
00:36:54,587 --> 00:36:56,923
and all the attention they were getting.

694
00:36:59,383 --> 00:37:02,386
You could imagine him saying,
"That should be me."

695
00:37:03,137 --> 00:37:04,555
Unbelievable!

696
00:37:04,639 --> 00:37:07,600
It hit me like
I put my finger in a light socket.

697
00:37:07,683 --> 00:37:10,478
The times were edgy.
People were tired of the good guys.

698
00:37:10,561 --> 00:37:13,773
The milkshake men in the back of the yard
and all that milkshake crap.

699
00:37:13,856 --> 00:37:17,151
They were ready
for some edgy Mack 10 stuff for life.

700
00:37:17,235 --> 00:37:19,570
They were ready for some gangster stuff.

701
00:37:20,529 --> 00:37:23,324
I went, "Okay. I think I get it now."

702
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:30,289
Bash at the Beach, 1996,
changed the wrestling business.

703
00:37:30,373 --> 00:37:32,333
Completely changed it.

704
00:37:32,416 --> 00:37:35,503
So I was actually there as a kid,

705
00:37:35,586 --> 00:37:38,089
and the energy in that building was…

706
00:37:38,172 --> 00:37:40,591
It was so perfect
for what was about to happen.

707
00:37:43,970 --> 00:37:47,723
because it was just
such an emotional and sensory overload.

708
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:53,562
It was better than a high.
I've done my share.

709
00:37:53,646 --> 00:37:56,565
And this was like the best high
I've ever been on.

710
00:37:56,649 --> 00:37:59,652
Hulk Hogan is here! Hulk Hogan's here!

711
00:38:00,152 --> 00:38:02,488
Hulk Hogan is in the building!

712
00:38:02,571 --> 00:38:05,116
You're damn right he is!

713
00:38:05,199 --> 00:38:07,243
He wasn't announced. Wasn't advertised.

714
00:38:07,326 --> 00:38:09,578
We didn't know
'til he walked through the curtain.

715
00:38:10,955 --> 00:38:12,456
The audience was reacting.

716
00:38:12,540 --> 00:38:15,960
They think their hero's coming down
to save the other hero, right?

717
00:38:16,043 --> 00:38:18,337
We hated that Hulk Hogan.

718
00:38:18,421 --> 00:38:22,717
That do-gooder, clinch-jaw face
that he had when he came to help Hart.

719
00:38:22,800 --> 00:38:25,761
It's like, "He's coming
to put himself in the spotlight."

720
00:38:25,845 --> 00:38:27,388
"Not, not this again."

721
00:38:28,139 --> 00:38:30,683
You know, between the whole steroid thing

722
00:38:30,766 --> 00:38:34,145
and fans thinking
the red and yellow was dead,

723
00:38:35,980 --> 00:38:37,982
I just flipped the script on 'em

724
00:38:38,065 --> 00:38:41,694
and give them something
they'll never forget as long as they live.

725
00:38:43,321 --> 00:38:44,655
Hulk, Hulk, Hulk!

726
00:38:44,739 --> 00:38:47,408
-What has he done?
-Oh my God!

727
00:38:47,491 --> 00:38:49,660
What the hell is going on here?

728
00:38:49,744 --> 00:38:52,913
Hulk Hogan has betrayed WCW!

729
00:38:56,709 --> 00:38:58,336
There's a kid behind me,

730
00:38:58,419 --> 00:39:00,504
and he asked
the simplest question to his dad.

731
00:39:00,588 --> 00:39:04,008
He literally just said,
"Dad, why did he do that?"

732
00:39:04,091 --> 00:39:05,926
He's a bad guy now.

733
00:39:10,014 --> 00:39:12,433
One, two, three!

734
00:39:13,976 --> 00:39:17,188
There's this moment of silence.

735
00:39:18,064 --> 00:39:19,273
It doesn't take you long

736
00:39:19,357 --> 00:39:22,026
before you realize
you're in a riot situation,

737
00:39:22,109 --> 00:39:26,989
and they wanted to come
and pull you apart like the living dead.

738
00:39:28,616 --> 00:39:32,703
We got a fan coming in
to try to help matters out.

739
00:39:37,249 --> 00:39:38,667
He didn't last long.

740
00:39:41,337 --> 00:39:47,176
I felt like it was a classic case of…
innocence lost.

741
00:39:48,761 --> 00:39:53,099
Hulk Hogan, excuse me, excuse me.

742
00:39:55,267 --> 00:39:58,521
What in the world are you thinking?

743
00:40:00,064 --> 00:40:05,069
Mean Gene, the first thing you need to do
is to tell these people to shut up

744
00:40:05,152 --> 00:40:07,488
if you want to hear what I gotta say!

745
00:40:08,614 --> 00:40:10,699
Then it got evil in there, man.

746
00:40:10,783 --> 00:40:13,619
As soon as I saw
Mean Gene's nose get split open,

747
00:40:13,702 --> 00:40:16,163
and I plugged into that crowd.

748
00:40:16,247 --> 00:40:18,249
My mindset is to screw the audience.

749
00:40:18,332 --> 00:40:24,171
All this crap in the ring
represents these fans out here.

750
00:40:24,255 --> 00:40:27,133
I did everything for the charities.

751
00:40:27,216 --> 00:40:29,927
I did everything for the kids.

752
00:40:30,010 --> 00:40:33,848
And the reception I got
when I came out here,

753
00:40:33,931 --> 00:40:36,434
you fans can stick it, brother.

754
00:40:36,517 --> 00:40:40,563
There was parts of him that wanted
to let people know what he really thought.

755
00:40:40,646 --> 00:40:42,940
It felt great.

756
00:40:43,524 --> 00:40:45,943
There was so much heat. It was incredible.

757
00:40:46,026 --> 00:40:48,988
I looked at people in the eyes,
at five feet away from me,

758
00:40:49,071 --> 00:40:50,156
and they wanted to kill me.

759
00:40:50,239 --> 00:40:53,993
They had blood coming out
of their eyeballs 'cause they were so mad.

760
00:40:54,076 --> 00:40:57,580
I knew I could just rule.
I could rule the business.

761
00:40:57,663 --> 00:41:01,667
This right here
is the future of wrestling!

762
00:41:01,750 --> 00:41:07,673
You can call this the New World Order
of wrestling, brother.

763
00:41:07,756 --> 00:41:09,884
What you gonna do? What are you gonna do?

764
00:41:09,967 --> 00:41:12,511
Don't touch me.
I've got a fleet of lawyers.

765
00:41:13,971 --> 00:41:18,726
I remember him saying like, "You know
all the red and yellow, good guy stuff?"

766
00:41:18,809 --> 00:41:20,936
"That's out the window.
I'm a bad guy now."

767
00:41:21,020 --> 00:41:24,106
Here we go. Can everybody see that? And…

768
00:41:25,107 --> 00:41:26,275
He was crazy.

769
00:41:26,859 --> 00:41:29,820
Hulk doesn't work anymore.

770
00:41:29,904 --> 00:41:33,866
He said, "Do I have any black,
patent leather boots? I have to go see."

771
00:41:33,949 --> 00:41:36,702
So I go in his closet, dig around.
I'm like, "These?"

772
00:41:36,785 --> 00:41:39,288
They're a hundred years old from 1965.

773
00:41:39,371 --> 00:41:41,123
He's like, "Yeah, those."

774
00:41:41,207 --> 00:41:42,333
You better get going.

775
00:41:42,416 --> 00:41:44,793
I'm going. I'm on time. I got two hours.

776
00:41:44,877 --> 00:41:47,963
I give him my black leggings.
He's like, "Yeah, that's it."

777
00:41:48,047 --> 00:41:50,341
Puts the belt around him.
I say, "That's it."

778
00:41:50,424 --> 00:41:53,802
Now, he's turned his back on it all.

779
00:41:53,886 --> 00:41:55,513
Ladies and gentlemen,

780
00:41:55,596 --> 00:42:01,477
Hollywood Hogan!

781
00:42:05,564 --> 00:42:07,566
Nothing was ever the same after that.

782
00:42:08,526 --> 00:42:12,488
If Hulk Hogan can turn heel,
then anything can happen.

783
00:42:13,405 --> 00:42:18,911
Hulk was trying to fit
into this new world, this new society.

784
00:42:18,994 --> 00:42:20,996
And it worked tremendously.

785
00:42:22,623 --> 00:42:26,043
He has one of the greater changes
in all the history of our industry.

786
00:42:26,126 --> 00:42:28,045
-My gosh.
-It flips everything.

787
00:42:28,128 --> 00:42:31,173
I laid it out straight
for all those kids, brother.

788
00:42:31,257 --> 00:42:34,593
They didn't want to follow the path,
so I'm done with them!

789
00:42:34,677 --> 00:42:36,804
Hulkster was doing it out of anger.

790
00:42:36,887 --> 00:42:38,931
He was the shit, you know.

791
00:42:39,014 --> 00:42:40,724
He was the dude.

792
00:42:40,808 --> 00:42:43,102
You piece of trash.

793
00:42:43,185 --> 00:42:47,856
You know, the cheap shots
and the dastardly evil type character,

794
00:42:47,940 --> 00:42:49,692
like a Batman villain.

795
00:42:50,734 --> 00:42:53,779
He wasn't afraid to break the rules.

796
00:42:53,862 --> 00:42:56,574
You know, take over the announcer's table.

797
00:42:56,657 --> 00:42:59,368
Is there any question now?

798
00:42:59,451 --> 00:43:04,248
Who is the most powerful man
in professional wrestling?

799
00:43:04,331 --> 00:43:07,001
He's yelling at old ladies?

800
00:43:07,084 --> 00:43:08,210
He's phenomenal.

801
00:43:11,505 --> 00:43:14,633
I don't have to play by any rules
as Hollywood Hogan.

802
00:43:14,717 --> 00:43:16,260
I can lie, cheat.

803
00:43:16,343 --> 00:43:19,096
Lie to your face and get away with it
because I'm a bad guy.

804
00:43:19,179 --> 00:43:22,266
Who made who? Who made you?

805
00:43:22,349 --> 00:43:25,394
If you made them and they made you
Who picked up the bill?

806
00:43:25,477 --> 00:43:27,438
Ooh, and who made who?

807
00:43:27,521 --> 00:43:30,316
You can't have that
without having the red and yellow.

808
00:43:30,399 --> 00:43:32,651
You know, it's a juggling act here.

809
00:43:32,735 --> 00:43:36,822
That duality of, like,
the good guy turned bad.

810
00:43:36,905 --> 00:43:38,699
Who turned the screw?

811
00:43:38,782 --> 00:43:40,826
It was the coolest thing he'd ever done.

812
00:43:40,909 --> 00:43:43,454
Nick is going on his trip with his dad.

813
00:43:43,537 --> 00:43:45,039
Can you zip this up?

814
00:43:45,122 --> 00:43:46,373
-This?
-Zip it up.

815
00:43:46,457 --> 00:43:48,375
So, you look so cute.

816
00:43:48,459 --> 00:43:53,839
It's my absolute favorite,
favorite era of his career.

817
00:43:53,922 --> 00:43:59,053
Hulk Hogan was changing
the mentality and the mindset of the fan,

818
00:43:59,136 --> 00:44:01,430
the purity,
the good guy against the bad guy.

819
00:44:01,513 --> 00:44:03,223
Unbelievable!

820
00:44:03,307 --> 00:44:06,101
And people gravitated to that.

821
00:44:06,185 --> 00:44:07,353
Hold him up.

822
00:44:08,270 --> 00:44:11,815
Who made you?
If you made them and they made you

823
00:44:11,899 --> 00:44:14,610
Who picked up the bill
And who made who?

824
00:44:17,613 --> 00:44:21,075
The more the crowd booed me,
the more evil I wanted to be.

825
00:44:21,158 --> 00:44:22,242
Who made who?

826
00:44:22,326 --> 00:44:24,453
I'd take my belt off
and whip the good guys.

827
00:44:27,456 --> 00:44:31,043
The people were
just cheering me out of the building.

828
00:44:32,670 --> 00:44:35,881
Isn't that crazy? He's beating
people up, doing everything you can

829
00:44:35,964 --> 00:44:38,467
to make people hate you,
and people loved him again.

830
00:44:40,094 --> 00:44:43,389
It was like Hulkamania in '84.
That vibe was there, man.

831
00:44:43,972 --> 00:44:45,891
I was up for another lightning bolt run.

832
00:44:45,974 --> 00:44:48,686
Turner Broadcasting's
WCW Monday Night Nitro

833
00:44:48,769 --> 00:44:53,399
has become one of the hottest two hours
of live programming each week on cable TV.

834
00:44:53,482 --> 00:44:58,237
Everybody in the country
wanted to be a part of the nWo.

835
00:44:58,320 --> 00:45:02,116
Who picked up the bill
And who made who?

836
00:45:04,326 --> 00:45:10,874
Well, it was so successful
it beat the WWE for 83 weeks.

837
00:45:11,458 --> 00:45:13,085
Who made you?

838
00:45:15,003 --> 00:45:19,717
So, I ended up basically… showing
Vince McMahon that he was wrong.

839
00:45:21,552 --> 00:45:22,970
And you know what?

840
00:45:23,053 --> 00:45:25,973
Now I'm gonna wish
a happy birthday to me, brother.

841
00:45:26,056 --> 00:45:28,475
To top this off, happy birthday, Linda.

842
00:45:28,559 --> 00:45:33,230
The reason we're in a wrestling mode
tonight is because…

843
00:45:33,814 --> 00:45:35,482
Put this over your shoulder.

844
00:45:35,566 --> 00:45:36,608
That's so heavy.

845
00:45:36,692 --> 00:45:38,610
We won the World Heavyweight Title

846
00:45:38,694 --> 00:45:41,321
for what,
the sixth or seventh time, Brutus?

847
00:45:41,405 --> 00:45:43,615
-Seventh.
-Seventh time.

848
00:45:43,699 --> 00:45:48,120
I don't recall who he was wrestling, nWo…
All that stuff is a blur in my mind.

849
00:45:48,203 --> 00:45:49,747
…the heavyweight title.

850
00:45:49,830 --> 00:45:52,040
I lost track because we were so busy.

851
00:45:52,124 --> 00:45:54,168
I had two kids out here.

852
00:45:54,251 --> 00:45:57,087
When I was gone, she handled everything.

853
00:45:57,171 --> 00:46:00,007
She didn't need…
She didn't need me around.

854
00:46:00,090 --> 00:46:02,426
They had him going more than anybody.

855
00:46:02,509 --> 00:46:08,307
And Brooke maybe had a Christmas concert,
or Nick might have had a soccer game,

856
00:46:08,390 --> 00:46:10,684
and he was out of town.

857
00:46:11,935 --> 00:46:14,438
When he was home, something changed.

858
00:46:14,521 --> 00:46:18,817
He just got kind of cold
and just wasn't really,

859
00:46:18,901 --> 00:46:21,612
I don't know, not… not my soulmate.

860
00:46:22,905 --> 00:46:26,033
I was just so unhappy.
I was just so lonely.

861
00:46:26,116 --> 00:46:27,451
I was just by myself.

862
00:46:28,035 --> 00:46:29,995
Well, it looks like it's gonna rain.

863
00:46:31,038 --> 00:46:32,581
Very rainy day.

864
00:46:33,248 --> 00:46:37,336
And I know it hurt the kids too,
because, gosh, "We want to be with Dad,

865
00:46:37,419 --> 00:46:41,006
but we can't be with Dad
because everybody wants to be with Dad."

866
00:46:41,089 --> 00:46:44,384
Y'all love this. This is life.
For life. Forever, baby.

867
00:46:44,468 --> 00:46:45,719
That's our bag, baby.

868
00:46:45,803 --> 00:46:49,223
There are some things
worth missing practice for, brother.

869
00:46:50,432 --> 00:46:53,894
And that's definitely the nWo, brother.

870
00:46:53,977 --> 00:46:55,187
They were partying,

871
00:46:55,270 --> 00:46:58,148
rolling up in the limousines,
flaunting and flossing.

872
00:46:58,232 --> 00:46:59,983
That's the way it was.

873
00:47:01,401 --> 00:47:04,363
When you're getting older,
you still want to be young.

874
00:47:04,446 --> 00:47:08,992
Yeah, I mean, you could really have
what's called a midlife crisis.

875
00:47:09,076 --> 00:47:12,246
I think, perhaps,
he went through that midlife crisis.

876
00:47:12,329 --> 00:47:15,541
I am God!

877
00:47:15,624 --> 00:47:20,712
It happens to a lot of guys
that aren't ready to let it go.

878
00:47:20,796 --> 00:47:23,590
But one thing
about, you know, Father Time,

879
00:47:23,674 --> 00:47:25,300
it waits for no man.

880
00:47:27,135 --> 00:47:31,223
Um, a couple things. Immediately post-op,
like tonight on the way home.

881
00:47:31,306 --> 00:47:34,768
Um, for whatever reason,
I'm sure you've had surgeries before.

882
00:47:34,852 --> 00:47:35,686
-No.
-No?

883
00:47:35,769 --> 00:47:37,980
-No.
-Okay. That's good, I think.

884
00:47:38,063 --> 00:47:40,440
Yeah. I don't know if it is or not now.

885
00:47:40,524 --> 00:47:44,152
Yeah, well, you did a lot
for not having surgery.

886
00:47:44,236 --> 00:47:48,866
You wouldn't think an athlete
could do anything on that type of knee.

887
00:47:48,949 --> 00:47:51,410
Obviously, he has a high pain tolerance.

888
00:47:51,493 --> 00:47:55,330
The injuries were getting there.
They were getting there.

889
00:47:55,414 --> 00:47:57,124
Because I blew my knee out

890
00:47:57,207 --> 00:48:00,961
on January 23rd, '84,
when I wrestled the Sheik,

891
00:48:01,044 --> 00:48:03,422
I had a knee that was blown
and needed to be fixed,

892
00:48:03,505 --> 00:48:06,049
but I just kept working on it forever.

893
00:48:06,133 --> 00:48:10,220
I lasted as long as I could
before I finally had my first scope job.

894
00:48:13,140 --> 00:48:14,766
I know what I wanted to ask you.

895
00:48:14,850 --> 00:48:17,644
-What about drinking alcohol afterward?
-You're fine.

896
00:48:17,728 --> 00:48:19,771
-I mean, tomorrow and stuff.
-Yeah.

897
00:48:19,855 --> 00:48:23,275
You know, I'd been grinding since '77.

898
00:48:23,358 --> 00:48:26,570
See, he let it go too long is the problem.

899
00:48:26,653 --> 00:48:30,198
-Was trying to be cool. It's not.
-A matter of time.

900
00:48:30,282 --> 00:48:31,450
You the man.

901
00:48:31,533 --> 00:48:33,076
That's what they used to say.

902
00:48:37,164 --> 00:48:40,083
He couldn't wrestle the way he used to
because of his injuries.

903
00:48:40,167 --> 00:48:42,628
He may have decided,
"I want to take some time off."

904
00:48:42,711 --> 00:48:46,340
He'll explore the other opportunities
that come his way because he's Hulk Hogan.

905
00:48:46,423 --> 00:48:50,385
This really helps me segue
into being the next president of the US.

906
00:48:50,469 --> 00:48:53,013
That's what I wanted. The next president!

907
00:48:53,096 --> 00:48:56,767
I had gotten so hot as a bad guy,

908
00:48:56,850 --> 00:48:59,603
I decided I was gonna be
the president of the United States.

909
00:48:59,686 --> 00:49:01,772
-Did you believe that?
-Yeah.

910
00:49:01,855 --> 00:49:03,774
Thank you. That's a strong statement.

911
00:49:03,857 --> 00:49:05,776
We can assume that's official.

912
00:49:05,859 --> 00:49:08,445
-What party? I'm curious.
-You know something?

913
00:49:08,528 --> 00:49:12,157
We are in heavy negotiations,
strategic meetings.

914
00:49:12,240 --> 00:49:15,118
You could debate Gore and Bush on issues?

915
00:49:15,202 --> 00:49:17,204
They'd have to bring me up to speed.

916
00:49:17,287 --> 00:49:20,040
I remember him with balloons and boas,
running for president.

917
00:49:20,123 --> 00:49:22,417
There's not a deeper storyline here.

918
00:49:22,501 --> 00:49:24,086
Storyline-wise, it was me.

919
00:49:24,169 --> 00:49:26,380
All I'd have to do is stand in the ring.

920
00:49:26,463 --> 00:49:27,714
You're kidding, right?

921
00:49:27,798 --> 00:49:28,799
No, I'm not kidding.

922
00:49:28,882 --> 00:49:32,344
Some of his ideas were
completely wacky and off the wall

923
00:49:32,427 --> 00:49:34,346
and almost, like, delusional.

924
00:49:34,429 --> 00:49:37,724
We really pushed hard
for about three months,

925
00:49:37,808 --> 00:49:40,644
and then I backed out. I just got scared.

926
00:49:40,727 --> 00:49:42,145
Thought I might win.

927
00:49:42,229 --> 00:49:44,815
I'm glad you're not coming into comedy.
Let me…

928
00:49:46,942 --> 00:49:49,569
All of the chaos that was going on.

929
00:49:49,653 --> 00:49:51,238
The finger wasn't on the pulse.

930
00:49:51,321 --> 00:49:53,198
The foot wasn't on the gas.

931
00:49:53,281 --> 00:49:55,534
It seemed like nobody was in control.

932
00:49:56,410 --> 00:49:59,079
If your deal is you're in charge,
and you got creative control,

933
00:49:59,162 --> 00:50:00,956
God bless you, man.

934
00:50:01,039 --> 00:50:05,002
Our job is to make sure
that we're as close to that as possible.

935
00:50:05,085 --> 00:50:08,839
One of the things me and Hulk did
was called the Finger Poke of Doom.

936
00:50:08,922 --> 00:50:13,468
We were in front of, like,
60,000 people in the Georgia Dome.

937
00:50:13,552 --> 00:50:15,470
We're gonna have a match.

938
00:50:15,554 --> 00:50:20,350
And you always knew
that, like, you were gonna get hit.

939
00:50:20,434 --> 00:50:23,353
But we were two big, giant guys
that were beat to shit.

940
00:50:24,855 --> 00:50:28,442
And I just heard him say, "Easy, brother."

941
00:50:28,525 --> 00:50:30,277
"We already got their money."

942
00:50:33,864 --> 00:50:35,615
What was that about?

943
00:50:35,699 --> 00:50:38,827
-One, two, three.
-What's going on there?

944
00:50:41,079 --> 00:50:43,999
All you're doing at this point
is just sort of messing with it.

945
00:50:44,082 --> 00:50:45,333
What happened?

946
00:50:45,417 --> 00:50:48,295
If they don't take you seriously as a fan,

947
00:50:48,378 --> 00:50:51,882
if they're not engaged with you,
you can't stay engaged with them.

948
00:50:52,883 --> 00:50:55,844
The Finger Poke of Doom
was justifiably seen

949
00:50:55,927 --> 00:50:58,764
as the moment
where it comes crashing down.

950
00:51:00,057 --> 00:51:03,977
The audience was ready to give up
on Hogan and the WCW.

951
00:51:09,191 --> 00:51:11,359
Next week begins a brand-new era.

952
00:51:11,443 --> 00:51:15,363
WCW creative team
has a brand-new direction.

953
00:51:15,447 --> 00:51:17,699
This Vince Russo guy came in.

954
00:51:18,992 --> 00:51:22,412
And he was the new head writer at WCW.

955
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:26,458
You know, he stepped up.
He had a different attitude.

956
00:51:26,541 --> 00:51:32,297
And I came really willing to do anything
I possibly could do to help this company.

957
00:51:32,380 --> 00:51:33,882
He kicked it off the hinges.

958
00:51:33,965 --> 00:51:35,717
Shut up, you old goats!

959
00:51:35,801 --> 00:51:37,761
Everyone of youse!

960
00:51:37,844 --> 00:51:40,764
Which one of you is passing the gas?

961
00:51:41,890 --> 00:51:43,975
You people stink, you old bags!

962
00:51:44,059 --> 00:51:46,478
He wanted to fire anybody over 40.

963
00:51:46,561 --> 00:51:49,773
You're just too damn old!

964
00:51:49,856 --> 00:51:51,566
There were high-priced players

965
00:51:51,650 --> 00:51:54,653
who didn't perform in the ring,
who went through the motions

966
00:51:54,736 --> 00:51:57,364
and collected their paycheck,
laughing all the way to the bank.

967
00:51:57,447 --> 00:51:59,658
This is gonna get ugly.

968
00:51:59,741 --> 00:52:02,494
They started
the Viagra on the Pole matches.

969
00:52:02,577 --> 00:52:06,248
Whoever wins gets the Viagra off the pole.

970
00:52:06,331 --> 00:52:07,749
It was disrespectful.

971
00:52:07,833 --> 00:52:09,084
It was really bad.

972
00:52:09,167 --> 00:52:11,962
The old boy's management is over!

973
00:52:12,045 --> 00:52:13,213
I was having problems.

974
00:52:13,296 --> 00:52:17,717
When you get done with surgery,
there's a real thin plastic bladder…

975
00:52:17,801 --> 00:52:19,302
I know I'm not done yet.

976
00:52:20,220 --> 00:52:22,514
Can I please get an autograph?

977
00:52:22,597 --> 00:52:24,891
We're really running behind tonight.

978
00:52:24,975 --> 00:52:29,646
He did everything to basically see
if he could undermine what I had going.

979
00:52:32,190 --> 00:52:34,693
The New Blood sending a message…

980
00:52:34,776 --> 00:52:36,903
It was ugly. Oh yeah.

981
00:52:36,987 --> 00:52:39,948
Russo was the poison,
the final nail in the coffin.

982
00:52:41,324 --> 00:52:43,243
I want to go back to the beach.

983
00:52:43,326 --> 00:52:45,495
Hogue went the hell home,

984
00:52:45,579 --> 00:52:49,541
and I promise everybody,
or else I'll go in the goddamn grave,

985
00:52:49,624 --> 00:52:52,502
you will never see
that piece of shit again!

986
00:52:56,173 --> 00:52:57,507
The harder they tried,

987
00:52:57,591 --> 00:53:03,597
they faltered into the point
of the company no longer being profitable.

988
00:53:03,680 --> 00:53:06,850
And the WCW
was put on the market for sale.

989
00:53:11,354 --> 00:53:15,734
I knew it was gonna crash and burn,
especially if I disappeared.

990
00:53:16,318 --> 00:53:17,903
And Vince McMahon went in.

991
00:53:17,986 --> 00:53:20,697
He bought it
for two and a half million bucks.

992
00:53:20,780 --> 00:53:22,824
So it was pretty crazy.

993
00:53:22,908 --> 00:53:29,623
Obviously, you all know
I have acquired WCW.

994
00:53:31,791 --> 00:53:34,127
That's right, I bought my competition.

995
00:53:37,130 --> 00:53:38,506
Mm.

996
00:53:38,590 --> 00:53:45,513
My, my
The clock in the sky is pounding away

997
00:53:45,597 --> 00:53:47,933
There's so much to say…

998
00:53:48,016 --> 00:53:50,018
He was in a slowdown period.

999
00:53:50,101 --> 00:53:52,020
Just our family unit together.

1000
00:53:52,103 --> 00:53:54,481
Everything was at peace,
knowing Dad was home.

1001
00:53:55,273 --> 00:53:56,441
We gotta go.

1002
00:53:56,524 --> 00:54:00,570
An overdub has no choice

1003
00:54:01,196 --> 00:54:03,907
But something was off.
I could always sense it.

1004
00:54:04,658 --> 00:54:06,284
-Hey, Terry.
-Hey, Linda.

1005
00:54:06,368 --> 00:54:07,494
Look at me.

1006
00:54:07,577 --> 00:54:09,162
-What's up?
-Hi.

1007
00:54:09,246 --> 00:54:10,372
I'm pretty intuitive.

1008
00:54:10,455 --> 00:54:14,709
Terry, he's not gonna hide his mood.
You knew if he was in a good or bad mood.

1009
00:54:14,793 --> 00:54:17,337
It was kind of all the time
not a good mood.

1010
00:54:18,838 --> 00:54:21,341
But the porpoise is laughing…

1011
00:54:21,424 --> 00:54:25,178
We'd built a beautiful home,
and we had beautiful kids.

1012
00:54:25,262 --> 00:54:26,721
What else do you need?

1013
00:54:26,805 --> 00:54:28,932
I was trying to be
everything in the bedroom

1014
00:54:29,015 --> 00:54:31,518
and trying to stay looking young,
looking good, going to the gym,

1015
00:54:31,601 --> 00:54:32,477
and my body was good.

1016
00:54:32,560 --> 00:54:35,480
I thought, "What am I not doing that
he's still looking for something else?"

1017
00:54:35,563 --> 00:54:37,357
Ugh!

1018
00:54:37,440 --> 00:54:39,234
Jesus Christ.

1019
00:54:39,317 --> 00:54:44,155
But I was really married
to the Hulk character more than Terry.

1020
00:54:44,239 --> 00:54:47,575
And with that comes an ego.

1021
00:54:47,659 --> 00:54:50,996
Everybody knows
I'm the greatest wrestler in the world.

1022
00:54:51,079 --> 00:54:55,417
-I made Vince McMahon millions of dollars.
-Folks, I need your attention.

1023
00:54:55,500 --> 00:54:58,795
-It's Linda's birthday!
-Now, attention.

1024
00:54:58,878 --> 00:55:00,547
Hollywood Hogan was the man.

1025
